name Oriental Muesli Crescents
serves 24 pieces 8
attrib Essen und Trinken
note Keeps for up to 4 weeks in a dry place.
tags cookies, MENA

# Preparation

- 100 g flaked almonds
- 50 g ground hazelnuts
- 25 g sesame seeds
Toast in a dry pan in two or more batches until golden.
-> toasted nuts

- 100 g dried apricots
@nodep
Finely dice the apricots.
-> apricots

- 4 sprigs fresh mint
@nodep
Finely chop the mint.
-> mint

- 375 g crunchy muesli
- 40 g flour
- 1 tsp cardamom, ground
- 1 tbsp cinnamon
- 1 tbsp rose water
- 0.5 tsp gingerbread spice
- "ground cloves"
= toasted nuts
= apricots
= mint
Combine everything.
-> muesli mixture

- 200 g sugar
@nodep
Melt in a saucepan.

- 275 g honey
@ muesli mixture
Add the honey to the sugar, then immediately mix with the muesli mixture and spread onto
a baking sheet lined with parchment. Place a second sheet of parchment on top and press
down evenly to smooth. Peel off the top sheet.

Bake at 160°C for 35 minutes (fan 140°C, 20-25 minutes).
Leave to cool slightly, then cut out crescents using a round cutter (10 cm Ø) or
alternatively cut into diamonds.
